description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pre-assessment Nurse, &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time - &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The pre-assessment team at Ashford &amp; St. Peters Hospitals Foundation Trust are recruiting. We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to join our team of experienced Pre-operative assessment nurses.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role involves face to face or telephone assessment prior to patients’ anticipated elective general or orthopaedic surgery to ensure that they are adequately prepared and fit for their operation to proceed safely. You will be working in a nurse led team liaising closely with our anaesthetic colleagues following local and national guidelines for pre- operative management of both day case and in patient procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have a&lt;strong&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;minimum of one years’&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;recent experience in an acute setting- medicine/Surgery/Orthopaedics or pre-assessment, be able to use your own initiative, and have a flexible attitude to your work. You must also possess excellent clinical, communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently working from the Ashford site, Monday to Friday however cross site and weekend working may be required in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, you will be working with a friendly, supportive and flexible team who are committed to providing an excellent service. We will also support your own personal development to help you enhance your skills and knowledge to work effectively and efficiently in your role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer access to the NHS Pension Scheme, work perks, NHS Discounts, opportunities for flexible working and access to onsite childcare provisions (nursery).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like further information regarding this post, please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Steph Sutch pre-assessment Sister on 01784 884626.&lt;/p&gt;
